.SH NAME
kthread_should_stop \- should this kthread return now?
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" kthread_should_stop
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

When someone calls \fBkthread_stop\fP on your kthread, it will be woken
and this will return true.  You should then return, and your return
value will be passed through to \fBkthread_stop\fP.
